PRIVACY.TITLE: PRIVACY POLICY
PRIVACY.CONTENT:
This privacy policy is included in the Terms of Use Agreement by reference.

Interface Agency collects and uses personal information for many purposes, including but not limited to, billing; product and service fulfilment; understanding client needs; website improvement; product and service improvement; transactions; communication with customers and potential customers regarding products and services and third party products and services. Clients’ private information will only be disclosed to Interface Agency's owners, employees, independent contractors, and service providers, acting on Interface Agency’s’ behalf or request. This is an example reference of an inline link.

INFORMATION COLLECTED BY THE ISP

The hosting provider for clients’ internet site has the ability to record various information, including domain name, pages accessed, date and time of access, web browser type and computer operating system, and referring information, and to disclose this information.

FINANCIAL INFORMATION FOR BILLING PURPOSES

When sales are made by Interface Agency, financial information must be disclosed. This information can include any number of facts Licensee is asked to provide, but most commonly includes name, financial / credit card information, billing address, and email address.

In the event Interface Agency receives financial/credit card information, we will not disclose it to anyone unless disclosure is required by law or a court order, or unless disclosure is required to address an issue implicated by the financial transaction. If client claims that their financial information was used to make a purchase they did not authorise, details about the financial transaction may be disclosed to law enforcement and anyone else deemed necessary to address the matter.

USE OF EMAIL ADDRESSES AND OTHER CONTACT INFORMATION

Interface Agency relies heavily on the use of email, telephone and the internet to provide information to the client and client expressly consents to receiving communications via email, text or voice message to cell phone, fax, telephone, mail, or any other delivery method.

Client agrees to receive information about the product or service purchased. This may include, but is not limited to, information about product or service updates, new features, or information Interface Agency believes the client may find interesting.

Interface Agency will not sell, provide, or transfer Licensees email address to others and will only send information about other products and services when they are related to a product or service already purchased, or form part of an upgrade to material.

Interface Agency does not allow advertising, or engage in joint marketing ventures. Client should not receive advertisements from third parties. If client does receive an advertisement claiming to be related to Interface Agency, that fact must be made known to us immediately.

IDENTIFICATION OF PURCHASERS

If the client purchases a product or service, and joins one of the online forums, client authorises us to use their name and correspond in the manner intended for that forum.

Interface Agency also uses personal information in an aggregate form (i.e., not individually attributable to Licensees) for business analysis, operational and marketing purposes.

COOKIES

Cookies may be used to monitor access to the website. Client consents to any future use of cookies for testing purposes and the use of cookies for publicly available data to gather statistics for the purpose of determining which search engines, referring sites, key words, etc., bring visitors to the website, which pages visitors are most interested in, what web browsers are used, etc. Various providers may be used for this purpose. The purpose is to obtain information that will help promote the website, make the website more interesting and useful to visitors, and to identify areas where improvement is needed. The client can control the use of cookies, including preventing their use, by adjusting the preferences in their web browser.

Additionally, various third party information suppliers and other entities that provide information for this website, or for use by Interface Agency, may use cookies. Examples include, but are not necessarily limited to billing providers and third party resources.

DISCLOSURE BY NECESSITY

Private information may be disclosed if required by a court order, statute, law, or regulation.

Information is subject to disclosure to address a claim that a client is violating the terms of any Agreement pertaining to their use of this website or products or services, or rights of any third party.

Information is also subject to disclosure if Interface Agency believes that disclosure is necessary to identify, contact or bring an action against someone who may be causing injury to or interfering (either intentionally or unintentionally) with our rights or property, clients rights or property, other users of the website, products or services, or anyone else.

Interface Agency may sell or buy other businesses or entities, or it may merge with another company, or be bought by another company. In such transactions, personal information may be one of the transferred assets.

Client information may be stored and processed in any country in which Interface Agency maintains facilities or conducts operations. By using this website, products and services, client consents to any such transfer of information.

After clients’ account becomes inactive their information may remain in Interface Agency’s databases, computers, and archives, and cannot reasonably be eliminated for a period of ten years.

CONSENT TO USE INFORMATION

When client communicates with Interface Agency, sends information, or provides content to the website, clients grants a non-exclusive, worldwide, perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free, sub licensable right to exercise all copyright and publicity rights they have in the content, in any manner whatsoever, in any media now known or which may be created in the future, including in other works and forms not associated with this website.
